 cue late enough to require attention but early enough to keep the rep safe.","Athlete solves the cue, tracks the object, catches or handles the ball, and finishes in control.","Athlete calls what they saw after the catch, then resets before the next attempt."],"coach_cues":["Turn safely, find the ball.","Eyes quiet before hands quick.","Solve the cue first.","Catch clean, then reset.","Stop before sloppy."],"common_faults":["Looking at the feet instead of the cue or ball.","Rushing the rep and guessing before the stimulus is clear.","Adding extra steps, hops, or body sway after the catch.","Catching with panic hands instead of soft hands and a stable finish.","Turning the drill into fatigue work instead of coordination practice."]}'::jsonb)
) AS d(name, slug, description, skill, age_min, sets, reps, work, rest, est, summary, coach_lang, athlete_lang, family, phase_key, subrole, slot, req, exec)
CROSS JOIN public.facility f
ON CONFLICT (facility_id, slug) DO NOTHING;

